docs.abstract: Ms. Omar, a member of the “Squad” of progressive women of color elected to the House two years ago, topped a well-funded challenger in a victory for the left.
docs.snippet: Ms. Omar, a member of the “Squad” of progressive women of color elected to the House two years ago, topped a well-funded challenger in a victory for the left.
docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Representative Ilhan Omar of Minnesota fended off a well-funded primary challenger on Tuesday, ensuring a clean sweep of re-election fights for the group of first-term Democratic congresswomen of color known as the Squad and sending a message to Washington about the staying power of the party’s new progressive voices.

headline.main: Ilhan Omar Wins House Primary in Minnesota

docs.abstract: A clash at a Maryland local shows the tensions in a labor movement whose ranks include law enforcement officers along with many nonwhite, nonpolice members.
docs.snippet: A clash at a Maryland local shows the tensions in a labor movement whose ranks include law enforcement officers along with many nonwhite, nonpolice members.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Gabriel Acevero, a Maryland state legislator employed by a union local, introduced a bill last year to roll back protections for police accused of misconduct, he was stepping on a potential fault line. His union, Local 1994 of the United Food and Commercial Workers, represents thousands of Black and Latino workers in food services and at a variety of government agencies. It also includes a small portion of workers in law enforcement.

headline.main: He Says a Union Fired Him Over His Push for Police Reform
headline.print_headline: Split in Labor  Over Calls To Rein In The Police

docs.abstract: In “Black Outlined Blue,” Daniel Edwards, the son of two law enforcement officials, examined the difficulties and insights of being both black and a police officer.
docs.snippet: In “Black Outlined Blue,” Daniel Edwards, the son of two law enforcement officials, examined the difficulties and insights of being both black and a police officer.
docs.lead_paragraph: Daniel Edwards was scrolling through his Facebook feed in the summer of 2016, when he came upon a viral video of Diamond Reynolds who, in a calm panic was recounting how a police officer in St. Anthony, Minn., shot and killed her boyfriend, Philando Castile, during a routine traffic stop.

headline.main: Black Cops on Both Sides of the Badge

docs.abstract: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.snippet: Angry counterprotesters far outnumbered the small band of far-right demonstrators who turned out in Washington, and then quickly dispersed, on the anniversary of the violent Charlottesville rally.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After weeks of hype, white supremacists managed to muster just a couple of dozen supporters on Sunday in the nation’s capital for the first anniversary of their deadly rally in Charlottesville, Va., finding themselves greatly outnumbered by counterprotesters, police officers and representatives of the news media.

headline.main: Rally by White Nationalists Was Over Almost Before It Began

docs.abstract: Kaatsbaan hosts a welcome summer festival in the Hudson Valley, where nature and dancers join forces to put on a show.
docs.snippet: Kaatsbaan hosts a welcome summer festival in the Hudson Valley, where nature and dancers join forces to put on a show.
docs.lead_paragraph: TIVOLI, N.Y. — It didn’t bode well that the first live dance I was going to see since mid-March was one I had seen many times before. “Sunshine,” a Larry Keigwin war horse set to the Bill Withers’s classic “Ain’t No Sunshine,” can give a dancer the opportunity to really feel the music in all the worst ways. It’s treacly stuff.

headline.main: What Is It Like to Watch Live Dance Again? Amazing
headline.print_headline: A Reminder That Live Dance Is Amazing
